	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				There is no &quot;role-playing&quot; in Everquest. Any attempts to role-play as you would in a pen and paper game are generally not welcomed. <BR>
<BR>
It's unfortunate because a real RPG with a group of friends is a lot of fun. <BR>
<BR>
Those die-hard fans who doubt me, can try my theory in-game by not allowing a member of an &quot;evil&quot; race into your group. See what the other player's reaction is. Try shouting for a new group member &quot;except necros or SK's&quot; because your group is &quot;good&quot;. <BR>
<BR>
The world of EQ is static-it doesn't change. There is no story. There are no consequences for anyone's actions. Players cannot affect the world around them. It's a giant game of Whack-a-Mole&quot; for prizes. <BR>
<BR>
Why am I angry? I paid $60 plus $10/mo. and spent many hours expecting an RPG. EQ is not role-playing despite its designers claims to the contrary. <BR>
<BR>
ucclear<BR>
<BR>
&quot;The two most common elements in the universe are hydrogen and stupidity.&quot;<BR>
-Harlan Ellison
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
